snippet.textDisplay:
I don't understand why people are so he'll bent on showing themselves against momina. It's like bashing her is becoming the new trend. So pathetic. Out of all the singers you pick someone and then everyone start pointing out mistakes. I'm not overly crazy about her voice either but that doesn't automatically say she is by any means less than a singer (I bet she's better than most of us) She's just a young girl, who has started out in the world of music, but sadly Pakistanis, men or women, like to pick on a young singer who isn't even used to the fame yet. And unfortunately for her, she has mostly attracted perverts and bashers. Perverts who are trying to compare her to the likes of a super model with equally dire backlash that she's normal/not that pretty/average. She never claimed to be a beauty queen. She's here to sing. Let her sing. And bashers are judging her to the likes of Lata, Noorjahan or any other renown artist. For goodness sakes, she's new. She's young. And she looks scared and nervous as hell. If this is how we treat young talent in our country, calling them parchi and all. Then no wonder they go to India or prefer some other country to work in. She lives in America and in her interview on BBC urdu she said that coke studio called her and asked her to send a voice sample but she was nervous and didn't want to get her hopes high in case they rejected her voice. I hope I drove my point home. Phew! 
Stay lit. Peace.
